    "text": "\"A little goes a long way\".......having just got my ink the other day and doing teeny-tiny test sections with it I was using a 2/3 inch artist's wash brush. Being a stingy Scot, rather than wash out the brush when I was done I dunked it in a soggy jar of paper pulp.....oh boy it turned jet black for the top 2 inches of the jar almost immediately. I was blown away by how much conductivey-goodness was in that nearly dry brush!",
